In C, you can terminate a program in several ways, but the most common and standard way is to use the `exit()` function from the `<stdlib.h>` library. Here's how you can use it:

```c
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {
    // Your code here

    // Terminate the program
    exit(0);  // Exit with success (status code 0)
    return 0; // This line will not be reached
}
```

